<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-18T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9964: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-18T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                        1928—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>163. Your telegram 360, May 17, 4 p.m., has arrived since the sending of
                            my telegram 162, May 18, 1 p.m. I am in entire agreement <pb facs="0345" n="227" xml:id="pg_227"/> with you and Generals Butler and Castner.
                            Your view of the situation is, in my opinion, correct.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>